legend>{{cite web |url=http://www.warsaw-life.com/poland/warsaw-legend |title=The Warsaw Mermaid |accessdate=11 February 2008}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=warsawuprising_com>{{cite web |url=http://www.warsawuprising.com/faq.htm#Warsaw%20Ghetto%20Uprising |title=Warsaw Uprising of 1944 |work=warsawuprising.com |accessdate=14 July 2008}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Wetering>{{cite book |first=Ernst |last=Wetering, van de |title=A Corpus of Rembrandt Paintings IV: Self-Portraits |year=2005 |page=245|chapter= |chapterurl= |publisher=Springer |isbn=14-02032-80-3 |url=}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=wilanow-palac>{{cite web |url=http://www.wilanow-palac.art.pl/index.php?id=343&menuid=136 |title=Palace |work=wilanow-palac.art.pl |accessdate=21 February 2008}}</ref>\n\n<!--ref name=Yearbooks>{{cite web |url=http://www.stat.gov.pl/gus/index_ENG_HTML.htm |title=Demographic Yearbooks of Poland 1939\u20131979, 1980\u20131994 |work=stat.gov.pl |publisher=Central Statistical Office of Poland |accessdate=29 August 2008}}</ref-->\n\n<ref name=Zamoyski>Adam Zamoyski, ''Warsaw 1920: Lenin's Failed Conquest of Europe'' (2008)</ref>\n\n<ref name=Zbiory>{{cite web |url=http://www.buw.uw.edu.pl/index.php?option=com_content&task=blogcategory&id=56&Itemid=121 |title=Zbiory g\u0142\u00f3wne |work=buw.uw.edu.pl |accessdate=30 January 2009|language=pl}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Zimmerman>{{cite book |author=Joshua D. Zimmerman |title=Poles, Jews and the politics of nationality |year=2004 |page=16 |chapter=|chapterurl=|publisher=University of Wisconsin Press |location=|isbn=0-299-19464-7 |url=https://books.google.com/?id=6sbr9cZyw_4C&pg=PA16&dq=population+Brest+Poles+Jews |accessdate=}}</ref>\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{Refbegin}}\n* {{Cite book|last=Crowley |first=David |title=Warsaw |url=https://books.google.com/?id=E4cM2Hf8KYsC&printsec=frontcover#v=onepage&q&f=false |accessdate=28 August 2011|edition=|year=2003|publisher=[[Reaktion Books]]|location=|isbn=1-86189-179-2|ref=}}\n* {{Cite book|last1=Olchowik-Adamowska|first1=Liliana|last2=\u0141awecki|first2=Tomasz|title=Travellers Warsaw|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=xXbqAQAACAAJ|accessdate=11 March 2010|edition=First|date=1 April 2006|publisher=[[Thomas Cook Group|Thomas Cook Publishing]]|location=[[Peterborough]], United Kingdom|isbn=978-1-84157-492-9|ref=Adamowska69}}\n* [http://www.e-warsaw.pl/index.php Official webpage of Warsaw] includes 360\u00b0 panoramas of the [http://www.e-warsaw.pl/miasto/unesco.htm UNESCO listed area.]\n* [http://mokotow.policja.waw.pl/?page=Structure&id=131 District Police Headquarters&nbsp;\u2013 Warsaw II] (part of Warsaw Metropolitan Police)\n* [http://www.warsawguide.com/ Warsaw Guide.] Online City Guide for Warsaw in Poland. Retrieved 17 May 2015.\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20160914074916/http://www.ourpoland.com/warsaw/what-to-do-in-warsaw/ What to do and see in Warsaw]\n{{Refend}}\n\n==Further reading==\n{{Main|Timeline of Warsaw#Bibliography|l1=Bibliography of the history of Warsaw}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Sister project links|voy=Warsaw}}\n* {{Official site|http://www.um.warszawa.pl/en}} {{in lang|en}}\n\n{{Navboxes\n|title= Articles related to Warsaw\n|list=\n{{Warsaw}}\n{{Mayors of Warsaw}}\n{{Districts of Warsaw}}\n{{Culture in Warsaw}}\n{{Principal cities of Poland}}\n{{List of European capitals by region}}\n{{Capital cities of the European Union}}\n{{World Heritage Sites in Poland}}\n{{European Capital of Sport}}\n{{Masovian Voivodeship |state=collapsed}}\n}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Warsaw| ]]<!--leave the empty space as standard-->\n[[Category:Capitals in Europe]]\n[[Category:Cities and towns in Masovian Voivodeship]]\n[[Category:City counties of Poland]]\n[[Category:Holocaust locations in Poland]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Silver Cross of the Virtuti Militari]]\n[[Category:World Heritage Sites in Poland]]\n", "text_old": "{{about|the Polish capital}}\n{{redirect|Warszawa}}\n{{Redirect|City of Warsaw|the Second World War fighter squadron|No. 316 Polish Fighter Squadron|the airplane that crossed the Atlantic in 1934|Adamowicz brothers}}\n{{short description|Capital of Poland}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2018}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                         = Warsaw\n| native_name                  = <small>''Warszawa''</small>\n| native_name_lang             = pl\n| settlement_type              = [[City with powiat rights|Capital city and county]]\n| image_skyline                = {{Photomontage|\n |color=#ffffff\n |photo1a = Warsaw panorama.png\n |photo2a = Pa\u0142ac Na Wyspie w Warszawie, widok na elewacj\u0119 po\u0142udniow\u0105.jpg\n |photo2b = Poland-00808 - Castle Square (31215382745).jpg\n |photo3a = Warszawa, ul. Nowy \u015awiat 72-74 20170517 002.jpg\n |photo3b = Warszawa, Rynek Starego Miasta 42-34 20170518 001.jpg\n |photo4a = Warszawa, ul. Krakowskie Przedmie\u015bcie 87, 89 20170516 003.jpg\n |photo4b = Warszawa, ul. Senatorska 10 20170516 001.jpg\n |photo5a = Wilan\u00f3w Palace.jpg\n | spacing = 2\n | border = 0\n | size = 276\n}}\n| image_caption                = <small>{{hlist|From top, left to right: [[Panorama|Warsaw Skyline]]|[[\u0141azienki Park]]|[[Royal Castle, Warsaw|Royal Castle]] and [[Sigismund's Column]]|[[Staszic Palace]] and [[Nicolaus Copernicus Monument, Warsaw|Copernicus Monument]]|[[Old Town Market Place, Warsaw|Main Market Square]]|[[Royal Route, Warsaw|Royal Route]]|[[Warsaw Old Town]]|[[Wilan\u00f3w Palace]]}}</small>\n| image_flag                   = Flag of Warsaw.svg\n| image_shield                 = [[File:POL Warszawa COA.svg|75px]]\n| nickname                     = ''Paris of the North, Phoenix City''\n| motto                        = ''Semper invicta''{{spaces|2}}<small>([[Latin]] \"Ever invincible\")</small>\n| mapsize                      = 230px\n| map_caption                  = Location within Poland##Location within Europe\n| pushpin_map                  = Poland#Europe\n| pushpin_relief               = 1\n| coordinates                  = {{coord|52|14|N|21|1|E|reg