airs\"] |language=Czech |trans-title=Prague \u2013 Twin Cities HMP |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130625205859/http://zahranicnivztahy.praha.eu/jnp/cz/partnerska_mesta/index.html |archivedate=25 June 2013 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|GEO}} [[Tbilisi]], Georgia<ref name=\"Tbilisi Sister Cities\">{{cite web|url=http://www.tbilisi.gov.ge/index.php?lang_id=ENG&sec_id=4571 |title=Tbilisi Sister Cities |accessdate=5 August 2013 |work=Tbilisi City Hall |publisher=Tbilisi Municipal Portal |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130724120155/http://www.tbilisi.gov.ge/index.php?lang_id=ENG&sec_id=4571 |archivedate=24 July 2013 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|ARM}} [[Yerevan]], Armenia<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.yerevan.am/en/partner/partner-cities/|title=Official website \u2013 Partner cities|work=yerevan.am|accessdate=28 March 2017}}</ref>\n\n==== Locations named after Warsaw ====\n; {{flagu|Canada}}:\n* [[Warsaw, Ontario]], near Peterborough;\n\n; {{flagu|United States}}:\n{{div col|content=\n* [[Warsaw (town), New York]]\n** [[Warsaw (village), New York]], within the town of Warsaw\n* [[Warsaw, California]]\n* [[Warsaw, Illinois]]\n* [[Warsaw, Indiana]]\n* [[Warsaw, Kentucky]]\n* [[Warsaw, Missouri]]\n* [[Warsaw, North Carolina]]\n* [[Warsaw, North Dakota]]\n* [[Warsaw, Ohio]]\n* [[Warsaw, Pennsylvania]]\n* [[Warsaw Township, Jefferson County, Pennsylvania]]\n* [[Warsaw, Texas]]\n* [[Warsaw, Virginia]]\n}}\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Poland|European Union}}\n* [[Battle of Warsaw (disambiguation)|Battle of Warsaw]]<!-- Link to disambiguation page, please do not change -->\n* [[Destruction of Warsaw]]\n* [[List of tallest buildings in Warsaw]]\n* [[List of honorary citizens of Warsaw]]\n* [[Street names of Warsaw]]\n* [[Tourism in Poland]]\n* [[Treaty of Warsaw (disambiguation)]]\n* [[Warsaw concentration camp]]\n* [[Warsaw dialect]]\n* [[Warsaw Fire Guard]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|refs=\n<ref name=Adamczyk>{{cite book |quote=The Soviet troops, ordered by Stalin to wait until the Germans had destroyed the remnants of Polish resistance, then moved into what was left of Warsaw, flushed out the remaining Germans, and proclaimed themselves liberators of the city. |author=Wesley Adamczyk |title=When God looked the other way: an odyssey of war, exile, and redemption |year=2004 |page=170 |location= |publisher=University of Chicago Press |isbn=0-226-00443-0 |url=https://books.google.com/?id=77sneNTXojQC&pg=PA170#v=onepage&f=false |accessdate=}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=aip1>{{cite web |url=http://www.aip.org/history/curie/polgirl2.htm |title=Polish Girlhood (1867\u20131891) |work=aip.org |publisher=American Institute of Physics |accessdate=25 February 2009}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=aip2>{{cite web |url=http://www.aip.org/history/curie/radinst1.htm |title=The Radium Institute (1919\u20131934) |work=aip.org |publisher=American Institute of Physics |accessdate=25 February 2009}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=aish>{{cite web|url=http://www.aish.com/holocaust/overview/he05n27.htm |title=The Warsaw Ghetto Uprising |work=aish.com |accessdate=29 July 2008 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080623220055/http://www.aish.com/holocaust/overview/he05n27.htm |archivedate=23 June 2008 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Ascheron>{{cite web |author=Neal Ascheron |url=http://www.halat.pl/poland2.html |title=The Struggles for Poland |work=halat.pl|accessdate=24 July 2008}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Baker>{{cite book |author1=Mark Baker |author2=Kit F. Chung |title=Frommer's Poland|year=2009|page=79|pages=|chapter=|chapterurl=|publisher=Frommer's|location=|isbn=0-470-15819-0|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ypJ5fzK_uSkC&printsec=frontcover#v=onepage&q&f=false|accessdate=}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Blewaska>{{cite web |author=Joanna Blew\u0105ska |url=http://wyborcza.pl/1,76842,5999966,Warszawa_da_sie_lubic_.html |title=Warszawa da si\u0119 lubi\u0107?|work=Gazeta Wyborcza |date=28 November 2008 |accessdate=29 September 2010|language=pl}}</ref>\n\n<